/Users/seanross/kingdom_of_god/home-base/current_hunts/big-thinkers/research-systems/codex-atlas/execution/agents/library/factual/yang-mills/shen-zhu-zhu-stochastic-analysis.md:76:1. **Tighter Hessian bound** (Option 2): The 8(d-1) factor is an estimate, not exact. A tighter counting might reduce the constant but cannot change leading behavior at large β. *An alternative approach* directly bounds sup|λ_min(HessS)| via D+C decomposition: a Decoherence Conjecture (||C(Q)|| ≤ 2(d+1), strongly supported numerically) gives a conditional β < 1/8 bound (1.5× improvement over Gershgorin-based β < 1/12); empirical adversarial search gives sup|λ_min| ≈ 14.73. See `hessian-lambda-min-adversarial.md`.
