/Users/seanross/kingdom_of_god/home-base/current_hunts/big-thinkers/research-systems/codex-atlas/execution/agents/library/factual/navier-stokes/vasseur-de-giorgi/chebyshev-sharpness-constant-field-extremizer.md:50:The Kato inequality |nabla |u|| <= |nabla u| could help in principle (nabla w_k = nabla |u| * 1_{|u|>lambda}), but for single-component div-free fields, Kato is tight (ratio = 1). For multi-component fields, Kato gap exists (ratio < 1 for shear flows) but helps the gradient/Sobolev step, not the Chebyshev step. **[COMPUTED]**
