/Users/seanross/kingdom_of_god/home-base/current_hunts/big-thinkers/research-systems/codex-atlas/execution/agents/library/meta/methodology/sign-flip-diagnostic-for-critical-thresholds.md:2:topic: Sign-flip diagnostic for locating critical parameter thresholds
/Users/seanross/kingdom_of_god/home-base/current_hunts/big-thinkers/research-systems/codex-atlas/execution/agents/library/meta/methodology/sign-flip-diagnostic-for-critical-thresholds.md:10:When two variants of a parameter bracket a qualitative threshold (one undershoots, one overshoots), the crossover gives a direct measurement of the critical parameter value. This is the **sign-flip diagnostic**: the sign reversal is more informative than either variant alone, because it pins the threshold.
/Users/seanross/kingdom_of_god/home-base/current_hunts/big-thinkers/research-systems/codex-atlas/execution/agents/library/meta/methodology/sign-flip-diagnostic-for-critical-thresholds.md:13:1. You have two variants on either side of a threshold
/Users/seanross/kingdom_of_god/home-base/current_hunts/big-thinkers/research-systems/codex-atlas/execution/agents/library/meta/methodology/sign-flip-diagnostic-for-critical-thresholds.md:17:The crossover value can be estimated by linear interpolation on the n-axis (or whatever parameter), giving the threshold directly from just two data points.
/Users/seanross/kingdom_of_god/home-base/current_hunts/big-thinkers/research-systems/codex-atlas/execution/agents/library/meta/methodology/sign-flip-diagnostic-for-critical-thresholds.md:25:1. **Design variants that you expect to straddle the threshold.** If you expect a sign reversal somewhere in [n_low, n_high], choose one point clearly below and one clearly above.
/Users/seanross/kingdom_of_god/home-base/current_hunts/big-thinkers/research-systems/codex-atlas/execution/agents/library/meta/methodology/sign-flip-diagnostic-for-critical-thresholds.md:27:3. **Estimate the threshold by interpolation.** If variant A gives Δ_A < 0 and variant B gives Δ_B > 0, the threshold is approximately: n* = n_A + |Δ_A| / (|Δ_A| + |Δ_B|) × (n_B − n_A).
/Users/seanross/kingdom_of_god/home-base/current_hunts/big-thinkers/research-systems/codex-atlas/execution/agents/library/meta/methodology/sign-flip-diagnostic-for-critical-thresholds.md:28:4. **Treat the threshold as the primary finding.** The critical value (here n*≈2.61, corresponding physically to the exact 3D electromagnetic ZPF spectrum) is often the scientifically meaningful result — not either variant individually.
