+# Exploration 001 Report
+
+## Executive verdict
+
+[VERIFIED] Decision target:
+
+  > Either there exists one preferred exact tiny-trigger object, with explicit smallness,
+  > delay, visibility, leakage, and back-reaction bookkeeping, that is sharp enough for
+  > Phase 1 support auditing, or every honest trigger definition either reduces to the
+  > previous five-role exact object or requires a non-canonical packet backup, so the
+  > strategy should stop early.
+
+[VERIFIED] Tao's theorem-facing trigger is `c` / `X3,n`, i.e. role `a3` in the exact helical notation inherited from the prior exact-circuit line.
+
+[CHECKED] Gate verdict: `fail`.
+
+[CHECKED] Stop category: `model-level negative candidate`.
+
+[CHECKED] One exact trigger object can be written cleanly in exact NS language, but it is not genuinely narrower than the prior five-role exact helical singleton object. It is that same object with trigger-centered observables attached to role `a3` and to the trigger-mediated channels `a2 a3 -> a3`, `a1 a3 -> a4`, `a4^2 -> a5`, and `a3 a4 -> a1`.
+
+[CHECKED] Because the preferred object collapses back to the already-killed five-role singleton circuit, it inherits the known structural obstruction: the monomial core `a1^2 -> a2`, `a1^2 -> a3`, `a2 a3 -> a3` cannot all be realized on singleton exact support.
+
+[CHECKED] The only backup is packetized. It fails the canonization gate immediately, so it cannot replace the preferred object as one theorem-facing exact-NS target.
+
+[CHECKED] Strategy implication: stop now. A restart would need to be a different mission whose first job is to canonize one packet model, not to continue Phase 1 on the present strategy.
+
+## Tao trigger map and role table
+
+[VERIFIED] Tao's reduced delayed-transfer circuit uses five causally linked roles:
+
+| Tao variable | Exact role | Meaning for the trigger question | Why it is unavoidable |
+| --- | --- | --- | --- |
+| `a` / `X1,n` | `a1(t) = u_{σ1}(k1,t)` | current carrier | needed to measure trigger smallness relative to the active carrier and to record back-reaction |
+| `b` / `X2,n` | `a2(t) = u_{σ2}(k2,t)` | slow clock / gate opener | needed because the trigger is delayed by amplifier input from the clock |
+| `c` / `X3,n` | `a3(t) = u_{σ3}(k3,t)` | tiny trigger | the theorem-facing trigger variable |
+| `d` / `X4,n` | `a4(t) = u_{σ4}(k4,t)` | conduit / rotor leg | needed because post-threshold trigger visibility is through the conduit/rotor activation |
+| `ã` / `X1,n+1` | `a5(t) = u_{σ5}(k5,t)` | next carrier / output | needed because successful delayed transfer must become visible at the handoff output |
+
+[CHECKED] This already answers the first helpful question. A "tiny delayed trigger" cannot be defined honestly as less than a five-role object if "dynamically decisive" means what it means in Tao's mechanism. The trigger is only meaningful through a carrier scale, a clocked amplifier, a conduit, and an output handoff.
+
+[VERIFIED] The exact representation is the helical Fourier basis on a finite sign-closed support
+
+```text
+S(K,σ) = {(kj,σj), (-kj,-σj) : j = 1,...,5},
+```
+
+with exact amplitude equations
+
+```text
+(∂t + ν|kj|^2) aj = Fj^des(a) + Fj^int-leak(a) + Fj^ext-leak(u).
+```
+
+[VERIFIED] The desired source-pair bookkeeping inherited from the prior exact object is
+
+```text
+D1 = {(3,4)},
+D2 = {(1,1)},
+D3 = {(1,1), (2,3)},
+D4 = {(1,3)},
+D5 = {(4,4)}.
+```
+
+[CHECKED] Trigger-centered notation table:
+
+| Quantity | Definition | Type |
+| --- | --- | --- |
+| Representation | exact helical amplitudes `aj(t)=u_{σj}(kj,t)` on `S(K,σ)` | exact NS data |
+| Trigger variable | `a3` | exact NS data |
+| Tao roles needed for causal meaning | `a1,a2,a3,a4,a5` | exact NS data |
+| Pre-threshold smallness | `T_pre(t) := |a3(t)| / max(|a1(t)|, eps_floor)` | exact observable with user floor |
+| Trigger amplifier witness | `V_amp(t) := |F3^amp(t)| / max(|F3^seed(t)| + |F3^int-leak(t)| + |F3^ext-leak(t)|, eps_floor)` | exact observable with user floor |
+| Downstream visibility witness | `V_out(t) := min( |F4^rot(t)| / max(|F4^int-leak(t)| + |F4^ext-leak(t)|, eps_floor), |F5^hand(t)| / max(|F5^int-leak(t)| + |F5^ext-leak(t)|, eps_floor) )` | exact observable with user floor |
+| Precursor leakage witness | `Leak_trig(t) := Σ_{j=3}^5 (|Fj^int-leak(t)| + |Fj^ext-leak(t)|)` | exact amplitude-level leakage ledger |
+| Back-reaction witness | `BR_trig(t) := |F1^back(t)| + |F1^int-leak(t)| + |F1^ext-leak(t)|` | exact amplitude-level carrier feedback ledger |
+| Threshold / delay condition | there exists `t_*` with `T_pre(t) <= η_act` for `t < t_*`, and `V_amp(t), V_out(t) >= λ` on `[t_*, t_* + Δ_delay]` | user-chosen admissibility rule on exact observables |
+
+[CHECKED] The exact desired pieces named above are:
+
+```text
+F3^seed  : (1,1) -> 3,
+F3^amp   : (2,3) -> 3,
+F4^rot   : (1,3) -> 4,
+F5^hand  : (4,4) -> 5,
+F1^back  : (3,4) -> 1.
+```
+
+[CHECKED] Pressure / Leray is not a separate story here. It is the mechanism that fixes the exact coefficients inside every `Fj^des`, `Fj^int-leak`, and `Fj^ext-leak`, and therefore enforces both rigidity and leakage in the trigger ledger.
+
+## Preferred exact object
+
+[CHECKED] Preferred object:
+
+```text
+T_pref = (S(K,σ), a1,...,a5, D1,...,D5, I ; Θ_trig).
+```
+
+[CHECKED] Here `S(K,σ)` and the exact helical coefficients are exact-NS data, while
+
+```text
+Θ_trig = (η_act, λ, Δ_delay, eps_floor)
+```
+
+is the user-chosen admissibility list for tiny-before-threshold, post-threshold dominance, and the allowed activation window.
+
+[CHECKED] Exact-NS data versus tolerances:
+
+| Component | Status |
+| --- | --- |
+| wavevectors `kj`, helicities `σj`, sign-closed support `S(K,σ)` | exact NS data |
+| amplitudes `aj`, exact helical triad coefficients, Leray-projected triad law | exact NS data |
+| desired source-pair sets `D1,...,D5` and the induced `Fj^des/Fj^int-leak/Fj^ext-leak` split | exact NS data once `(K,σ)` is fixed |
+| `η_act`, `λ`, `Δ_delay`, `eps_floor` | user-chosen admissibility parameters |
+
+[CHECKED] This is the narrowest honest exact trigger object because any attempt to delete one of the other four roles breaks one of the required trigger clauses:
+
+- without `a1`, "tiny" has no exact carrier-scale reference and back-reaction cannot be recorded;
+- without `a2`, the trigger loses its delayed amplifier channel;
+- without `a4`, the trigger cannot become causally visible in a transfer conduit;
+- without `a5`, there is no exact output witness that the trigger changed the next-shell handoff.
+
+[CHECKED] Direct answer to the mandated narrowness question:
+
+```text
+No. The preferred object is not genuinely narrower than the prior five-role near-closed circuit.
+It is that same exact object, with role a3 singled out by extra smallness/visibility/leakage/back-reaction bookkeeping.
+```
+
+[CHECKED] This collapse back to the prior object matters immediately. The preferred trigger object still contains the exact singleton monomial core
+
+```text
+a1^2 -> a2,
+a1^2 -> a3,
+a2 a3 -> a3,
+```
+
+so the known singleton non-embeddability result is inherited without any new support audit.
+
+[CHECKED] Dead end encountered while checking historical context: the older predecessor exploration-001 report temporarily treated packet roles as the preferred Phase 0 object. I rejected that route here because the later factual record and the current mission preload explicitly restore amplitude-level helical bookkeeping as primary and demote packetization to backup-only status.
+
+## Backup object and canonization verdict
+
+[CHECKED] Backup object, kept only for the required gate:
+
+```text
+T_pkt = (P1,...,P5, Π_pkt, Leak_pkt, Restore_pkt),
+```
+
+where each `Pj` is a packet of exact helical modes attached to Tao role `j`, `Π_pkt` is the packet coordinatization/projection, `Leak_pkt` is the packet-level leakage/back-reaction bookkeeping rule, and `Restore_pkt` is the rule for translating packet statements back into exact NS language.
+
+[CHECKED] Canonization gate:
+
+| Requirement | Verdict | Reason |
+| --- | --- | --- |
+| fixed support convention | `fail` | singleton failure only proves that some enlargement is needed; it does not select one exact packet support |
+| fixed projection / coordinatization | `fail` | packet amplitudes or energies depend on how the packet is projected after support choice |
+| fixed leakage / back-reaction bookkeeping | `fail` | desired-vs-leakage tables depend on both the support split and the chosen packet coordinates |
+| fixed restoration rule back to exact NS language | `fail` | no unique restored exact interaction network is singled out by the present data |
+
+[CHECKED] Canonization verdict: `fail`.
+
+[CHECKED] Therefore the packet backup is inadmissible for this strategy. It is not one exact object; it is an underconstrained family of repair attempts.
+
+## Precision gate analysis
+
+[VERIFIED] The trigger question can be written sharply at the amplitude level. So this is not a vague "NS is entangled" outcome.
+
+[CHECKED] But the sharpened object does not produce a new theorem-facing target. Causal trigger meaning forces the whole five-role exact ledger back in, and the preferred exact trigger object is identical, modulo highlighted observables, to the prior exact helical singleton object.
+
+[CHECKED] That means the strategy does not earn a fresh Phase 1 support audit. The only canonical object already inherits the prior structural obstruction, while the only wider backup fails canonization before any audit begins.
+
+[CHECKED] Direct answers to the remaining helpful questions:
+
+1. Can a tiny delayed trigger be defined as less than a five-role object?
+   No. Exact smallness, delayed amplification, downstream visibility, precursor leakage, and back-reaction together force the clock/amplifier/conduit/output/carrier bookkeeping back in.
+2. What exact quantity says the trigger is tiny before threshold?
+   `T_pre(t) = |a3(t)| / max(|a1(t)|, eps_floor)`.
+3. What exact quantity says the trigger becomes causally visible after threshold?
+   The paired dominance witnesses `V_amp` and `V_out`.
+4. What counts as precursor leakage or back-reaction?
+   `Leak_trig` is the coefficient-weighted amplitude-level leakage ledger on roles `3,4,5`; `BR_trig` is the carrier feedback ledger on role `1`.
+5. Does the preferred object inherit the prior singleton non-embeddability result?
+   Yes. Its desired monomial core is the same one already killed.
+6. If a packetized backup is proposed, is it really one object?
+   No. It remains an underconstrained family.
+
+[CHECKED] The right stop reason is therefore not "pressure is somehow generically bad." Pressure/Leray is the exact bookkeeping mechanism that prevents a trigger-only decoupling from becoming canonical and that enforces the inherited singleton rigidity.
+
+## Phase 1 recommendation or stop verdict
+
+[CHECKED] Stop verdict:
+
+```text
+fail
+category: model-level negative candidate
+```
+
+[CHECKED] Do not proceed to a new Phase 1 support audit inside this strategy.
+
+[CHECKED] The preferred object exists only as the already-killed five-role singleton candidate with role `a3` highlighted. The backup packet object fails canonization. That leaves no surviving exact tiny-trigger object for this strategy to audit.
+
+[CHECKED] The only sensible reopen path is a new mission of the form:
+
+```text
+define and defend one canonical exact packet model for Tao-like trigger roles
+before asking any support-audit, firewall, or construction question.
+```
+
+## Work log
+
+- Started report skeleton and decision target capture.
+- Read the required strategy, receptionist note, Tao delayed-transfer note, exact helical definition note, singleton non-embeddability note, spectator-coupling note, coefficient-rigidity note, packet non-canonicity note, and mission learnings note.
+- Checked predecessor strategy reports to distinguish superseded packet-first wording from the later stable amplitude-level factual record.
+- Used the prior singleton obstruction only as a fail-fast structural constraint, not as an excuse to reopen the full support audit.

